keyPolicies.policyTitle: Labour's Pledge for National Health Service
keyPolicies.policyDescription: Labour promises to build an NHS with the time to care, including 20,000 more nurses, 8,000 more GPs, joined up services from home to hospital, guaranteed GP appointments within 48 hours, and cancer tests within one week.

issues.health: Labour promises to build an NHS with the time to care, stressing the importance of 20,000 more nurses and 8,000 more GPs, along with joined up services from home to hospital. They commit to guaranteed GP appointments within 48 hours and cancer tests within one week.

images.caption: Labour's pledge includes commitments to the NHS, such as more nurses and GPs, improved patient service, and timely healthcare.
